args: We've reached the final round of\nthe Beauty on the Beach contest!
This one's for all the marbles!
Now then, let's meet the two beautiful\nladies who have emerged from the\nbattlefield that is the beach!
First, we have contestant #5,\nthe stunner of the seashore...Angie!
Tee hee! I'll do my best!
Next we have contestant #260,\na woman as enchanting as a cool\nocean breeze...Verica!
Er, it is a pleasure to meet you all.
This is our first all-female finals in a\ndecade! But who will emerge victorious?\nThat's for YOU—the audience—to decide!
You know what that means, ladies:\nTime to win over the crowd.
Hi, everybody! I'm Angie,\nthe stunner of the seashore!
I can't TELL you how much it would mean\nto be this year's Beauty on the Beach!
I hope I can count on your support!\nYou're the beeeeest!
Goodness, I'm ready to vote for her\nright now! But next, it's Verica's turn!
Er, hello. As a fortune-teller by trade,\nI don't have a tremendous amount of\nexperience with this sort of thing.
But hearing all of your cheers has\nfilled my heart with courage.
So I hope to steal the spotlight,\njust this one time.
Wow, listen to those cheers! Clearly both\nof these ladies have won a lot of hearts!
That brings us to the moment of truth...\nLet the voting begin!
Right now, the vote is tied...\nbut we have one ballot left!
It all comes down to this!
This year's Beauty on the Beach is...\nVericaaaaa!
I'm sorry, but I haven't voted yet.\n...And I'm voting for Angie.
The prize was hers for the takin'!\nWhy would she DO this?!
Angie, why don't you tell everyone why\nyou're so determined to win this contest?
When you explained it to me earlier,\nI found it impossibly cute and endearing.
I suspect that everyone else will be\nsimilarly charmed. ...Go ahead.
W-well, you see, I'm...\nI'm actually really shy.
But something made me gather up\nmy courage and enter this contest.
I had a message that I wanted to deliver\nto a certain someone, but I knew that I\nwasn't yet ready to do so.
Oh man, is this going where I think it is?!
Look at the longing in those eyes...\nThe woman is clearly in love.
Before this, I couldn't find the courage\nto confess my love to him. He just\nmeant the utter world to me.
So I challenged myself to become a person\nwho was as strong as my feelings for him.
*sniff* Ah, young love...\nIt's the damn best.
I remember how anxious I was when\nI first told my boyfriend I loved him!
The female vote appears to be shifting\ndramatically towards Angie.
Folks, this is unprecedented! And yet,\nall the votes have been cast...
Surely you cannot ignore the\nwill of the people?!
You seem much more energetic now\nthat you're arguing on behalf of\nsomeone else, you know that?
Are you certain about this?\nYou were going to win, you know.
Quite certain. I think I'm just happier\nletting others enjoy the bright lights.
Well, in that case... Our winner is Angie,\nthe young maiden in love!
Now you can tell him how you truly feel.
Oh, thank you, Verica.\nThank you, everyone!
I wish I was the guy she loves!
Yeah, I wanna see whoever this\nmystery man is!
Tell him now! Confess your love!
TELL HIM! TELL HIM! TELL HIM!
R-right here and now? I mean,\nI see him out there, but...
You have all the courage you need.
It's so strange, but I feel like I could do\nabsolutely anything with your support.
So I'm going to do it!
Give the people what they want, man!
Their happy faces have convinced me\nthat this was the best possible outcome.
Do you think Verica perhaps foresaw\nhow all of this would play out?
If so, I'm in awe of her talents.
And so, the ＂Beauty on the Beach＂ contest\nended...er...happily for everyone involved?
